<p class="p">The total energy used for the extraction of essential oils by means of MAHD method was calculated according to the following equation (Equation (2)):
 <disp-formula id="FD2-molecules-23-02866" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(2)</label>
  <math id="mm2" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mtext class="mtext"> </mtext>
     <mi class="mi">E</mi>
     <mi class="mi">C</mi>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mo class="mo"> </mo>
     <mfrac class="mfrac">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">P</mi>
       <mo class="mo"> </mo>
       <mo class="mo">×</mo>
       <mi class="mi">t</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mn class="mn">1000</mn>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
     <mtext class="mtext"> </mtext>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> in which, 
 <italic class="italic">EC</italic> (kWh) is the energy consumed, 
 <italic class="italic">P</italic> (W) is the power consumed during the extraction, and 
 <italic class="italic">t</italic> (h) is the extraction time. 
</p>
